# Typography & Responsive Layout

## Design tokens

Use `config/typography.ts` for all headings and section wrappers so mobile and desktop stay consistent.

### Typography (import from `@/config/typography`)

| Token | Use for | Mobile → Desktop scale |
|-------|---------|------------------------|
| `typography.headingPage` | Page title (h1) | text-2xl → sm:text-3xl → md:text-4xl → lg:text-5xl |
| `typography.headingHero` | Hero h1 only | text-2xl → … → xl:text-6xl |
| `typography.headingSection` | Section title (h2) | text-xl → sm:text-2xl → md:text-3xl → lg:text-4xl |
| `typography.headingCard` | Card/block title (h3) | text-lg → sm:text-xl → md:text-2xl |
| `typography.headingSmall` | Small heading (h4) | text-base → sm:text-lg |
| `typography.lead` | Lead paragraph | text-base → sm:text-lg → md:text-xl |
| `typography.body` | Body text | text-sm → sm:text-base |
| `typography.small` | Captions | text-xs → sm:text-sm |

### Layout (containers & spacing)

| Token | Use for |
|-------|--------|
| `layout.container` | Section content: `max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8` |
| `layout.containerNarrow` | Forms, single column: `max-w-2xl` + same padding |
| `layout.containerWide` | Hero, wide sections: `max-w-7xl` + same padding |
| `layout.sectionPy` | Section vertical padding: `py-10 sm:py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20` |
| `layout.sectionPySm` | Tighter sections: `py-8 sm:py-10 md:py-12` |

### Text colors (light/dark)

- `textColors.heading` — `text-gray-900 dark:text-white`
- `textColors.body` — `text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300`
- `textColors.muted` — `text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400`

## Rules

1. **No raw large types on mobile** — Avoid `text-4xl`, `text-5xl`, `text-6xl` without a smaller mobile size. Prefer `text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl …`.
2. **Use tokens in new components** — For any new section or page, use `typography.headingSection` (or appropriate level) and `layout.container` (or narrow/wide).
3. **Same structure everywhere** — Section wrapper: outer `<section className={layout.sectionPy}>`, inner `<div className={layout.container}>`, then content.
4. **Box/card padding** — Use `p-4 sm:p-6 lg:p-8` for cards and content boxes so they scale on small screens.
